{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"33c1179f-a44c-4c16-a616-b29ced6f5f43","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e8b3d405-1962-4fb6-9caf-56ae6f48f5a3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"0BD7:29D6CF:549D48:62C6E3:69F00970"},"id":"3815a85f-6be9-40a7-b401-206e758accae","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:12:23.399Z","parentId":"3a721f56-3497-4766-81ef-3cf0715d3d2a"}
